Exception handling - try throw catch

• notify caller error has occured
• the caller can catch the exception and handle it

try 
{ 
	- wrap the code that might throw an exception.
	- throw std::exception()
	- the runtime is prepared to catch and handle the exceptions 
		that might be thrown
	- the runtime searches for a catch block with a parameter that matches
		the type of the thrown exception
	- if exception occurs, the program jumps to corresponding catch
		
}
catch
{
	- where you handle the exception
	- excecute code to handle the error
	- the program can terminate or continue with the code that follows
}

throw
	- to signal that an error has occured
	- creates and throws an exception object, which can be caught and
		handled by a catch block

